            "id": "a9615c86320e4f6daf279",
            "questionText": "A seesaw consists of a uniform plank of length $!$4\\,\\text{m}$!$ and mass $!$10\\,\\text{kg}$!$, pivoted at its center. A child of mass $!$30\\,\\text{kg}$!$ sits at one end, and another child of mass $!$20\\,\\text{kg}$!$ sits $!$1\\,\\text{m}$!$ from the other end. If the seesaw is released from rest in this unbalanced configuration, what is its initial angular acceleration? Assume $!$g = 9.8\\,\\text{m/s}^2$!$.",
            "imageText": "",
            "steps": [
                {
                    "id": "8b4080936f7f4e4382f93",
                    "stepText": "Let's start by calculating the torques created by the children. To do this, first select the correct formula for the torque caused by a force applied at a distance from a pivot.",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        ""
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "",
                    "stepConcepts": [
                        "66c394e5-9b27-4235-9105-6b2e0ba0b2b0"
                    ],
                    "options": [
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = F \\times d$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": true
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = \\frac{F}{d}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        },
                        {
                            "optionText": "$!$\\tau = \\frac{d}{F}$!$",
                            "optionImage": "",
                            "isCorrect": false
                        }
                    ]
                },
                {
                    "id": "d0104864c5fd4a3495bfa",
                    "stepText": "Great! Now compute the net torque about the pivot. Remember that one child applies a torque in one direction and the other in the opposite direction. Use the appropriate distances and the gravitational force (calculated as mass multiplied by $!$g$!$). What is the net torque (in $!$\\text{N\\,m}$!$) about the pivot?",
                    "stepText2": "",
                    "stepImage": "",
                    "stepSolveAnswer": [
                        "392"
                    ],
                    "stepSolveAnswerUnits": "N\u00b7m",
                    "stepConcepts": [
